cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.SY 

This paper is about using resistive random access memories (RRAM) for implementing Binarized Neural Networks (BNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely categories include cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.EM (Electromagnetics), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
